parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle's electrical systems to malfunction, leading to loss of critical functions such as headlights, turn signals, and wipers, which can increase the risk of accidents. In some cases, it can also cause fires.
symptoms: The key turns too far and gets stuck
the ignition switch does not return to the normal position
the starter motor continues to run
lights and blower motors fail to come on
the key has to be manually turned back to the run position
the ignition switch feels soft or spongy
the electrical systems malfunction
and the vehicle loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The proximity of the battery to the rear seat suspension wires can cause a fire hazard, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The rear seat was shifted
causing the spring wires to contact the battery posts
igniting a fire
and spreading through the entire rear seat of the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank valve nipple can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, or other accidents, potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel leaks under the vehicle
strong fuel odor
fuel puddles near the rear end of the vehicle
fuel dripping onto the exhaust system
fuel traveling up the exhaust system towards the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accumulation of ice in the throttle housing can cause unintended acceleration, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the throttle becomes stuck
the vehicle is difficult to control
the vehicle continues to move even when the brake is applied.
